{{Infobox government agency |agency_name = Ministry of Culture and Tourism of the People's Republic of China |nativename_a = {{lang|zh-Hans|中华人民共和国文化和旅游部}} |nativename_r = {{small|''Zhōnghuá Rénmín Gònghéguó Wénhuà hé lǚyóubù}} |logo = |logo_width = |logo_caption = |seal = National Emblem of the People's Republic of China.svg |seal_width = 150px |seal_caption = [[Emblem of the People's Republic of China]] |formed = {{Start date|2018|03|19}} |preceding1 = |preceding2 = |dissolved = |superseding = |jurisdiction = {{PRC}} |headquarters = [[Beijing]] |employees = |budget = |minister1_name = [[Luo Shugang]]<ref>{{cite news|author= |url=http://www.chinadaily.com.cn/a/201803/19/WS5aaf1a7aa3106e7dcc1426fd.html |title=China's new cabinet members endorsed |newspaper=Chinadaily |date=2018-03-19 |language=}}</ref> |minister1_pfo = |parent_agency = [[State Council of the People's Republic of China|State Council]] |child1_agency = |child2_agency = |website = [http://www.mcprc.gov.cn/ http://www.mcprc.gov.cn/] |footnotes = }} {{Politics of China |expanded = Publicity }}
The '''Ministry of Culture and Tourism''' ({{zh |s = 中华人民共和国文化和旅游部 |t = 中華人民共和國文化和旅遊部 |p = Zhōnghuá Rénmín Gònghéguó Wénhuà hé lǚyóubù}}) is a [[Ministries of the People's Republic of China|ministry]] of the [[State Council of the People's Republic of China]] which is responsible for cultural policy and activities and tourism in the country. Its headquarters are in [[Chaoyang District, Beijing]]. It was formed on 19 March 2018; its predecessors were the [[Ministry of Culture of the People's Republic of China|Ministry of Culture]] and [[China National Tourism Administration]].<ref>{{cite news |author= |url = http://m.sohu.com/a/225429668_114988 |script-title = zh:文化部、国家旅游局合并为“文化和旅游部” |website = Sohu |date=2018-03-13 |language=zh }}</ref>
==History== On March 19, 2018, the [[Government of the People's Republic of China]] announced that the [[Ministry of Culture of the People's Republic of China|Ministry of Culture]] and [[China National Tourism Administration]] have been merged to create the Ministry of Culture and Tourism at the first session of the [[13th National People's Congress]]. That same day, [[Luo Shugang]] was elected Minister of Culture and Tourism.<ref>{{cite news|author= |url=http://www.ce.cn/culture/gd/201803/19/t20180319_28524714.shtml |script-title=zh:雒树刚被任命为首位文化和旅游部部长（附简历） |newspaper=ce.cn |date=2018-03-19 |language=zh}}</ref>
