{{Orphan|date=February 2009}} {{Infobox book | italic title = <!--(see above)--> | name = The No-Nonsense Guide to Globalization | image = The No-Nonsense Guide to Globalization.jpg | image_size = | alt = | caption = | author = Wayne Ellwood | audio_read_by = | title_orig = | orig_lang_code = | title_working = | translator = | illustrator = | cover_artist = | country = | language = | series = | release_number = | subject = | genre = | set_in = | publisher = Verso Books | publisher2 = | pub_date = 2001 | english_pub_date = | published = | media_type = | pages = 144 | awards = | isbn = 1-89635-746-6 | isbn_note = | oclc = | dewey = | congress = | preceded_by = | followed_by = | native_wikisource = | wikisource = | notes = | exclude_cover = | website = }}
'''''The No-Nonsense Guide to Globalization''''' is a book by [[Wayne Ellwood]], an editor for the ''[[New Internationalist]]''. It was first published in 2001 by [[Verso Books]].
It covers topics such as [[globalization]] around the world, the [[Bretton Woods Institutions]], [[developing countries' debt]], poverty, the environment, and possible means of redesigning the global economy.
==Reception== Sue McGregor of the [[International Journal of Consumer Studies]] said ''The No-Nonsense Guide to Globalization'' provided readers encouragement on how to change globalization.<ref>{{cite journal|last1=McGregor|first1=Sue|title=The no-nonsense guide to globalization |journal=International Journal of Consumer Studies|date=June 2002|volume=26|issue=2 |page=164|doi=10.1046/j.1470-6431.2002.t01-1-00236.x}}</ref>
